 retirement goal record with target retirement age, desired income/lump sum, and other goal parameters.\n   - Ensure the plan type/plan objective is tagged as **Retirement Planning / Retirement** so that downstream product selection and reporting recognise it as a retirement plan. \n\n4. **Collect and validate financial data**  \n   - Capture client income, expenses, assets, liabilities, existing investments, insurance, and tax details.\n   - Validate that the data is complete and consistent with KYC and existing system records.\n\n5. **Analyse current position and gaps**  \n   - Perform cash-flow and surplus analysis.\n   - Assess existing retirement assets and projected values.\n   - Identify the retirement funding gap versus the client’s goal.\n\n6. **Design retirement investment strategy**  \n   - Translate the gap into recommended contribution amounts, investment mix, and timelines.\n   - Select suitable products/securities that are enabled for **Retirement Planning** plan type/objective. \n\n7. **Simulate scenarios and validate suitability**  \n   - Run projections for different return, inflation, and contribution scenarios.\n   - Check alignment with the client’s risk profile, time horizon, and liquidity needs.\n\n8. **Prepare and present the retirement plan**  \n   - Generate a retirement plan/goal report summarising assumptions, projections, and recommended actions.\n   - Review with the customer and capture their consent/acknowledgement as per governance.\n\n9. **Translate the plan into transactions (implementation)**  \n   - For new investments or switches, place orders via the PMS/RM office application.   \n   - Ensure correct transaction types (purchase, SIP, switch, redemption) and correct amount/units input and validation rules are followed. \n\n10. **Monitor, document, and report**  \n   - Track all investment orders related to the retirement plan through the Order Book and Order Book Report for status and audit.    \n   - Periodically review the retirement goal vs. actual portfolio performance and update plan data as needed.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Data You Need to Collect (by Category)\n\n### 2.1 Customer and Regulatory Data\n\nCollected or confirmed as part of onboarding/KYC, then reused for retirement planning:\n\n- **Identification & demographics**  \n  - Full name, date of birth (to derive current age and retirement horizon)  \n  - Gender, marital status, dependants  \n  - Contact details (address, email, phone)\n\n- **KYC and regulatory**   \n  - KYC status (e.g., Registered / Under process) – must not be in a blocked state for transactions   \n  - Nationality/citizenship and residency status  \n  - Tax status (e.g., resident, NRE/NRO, foreign investor), as certain tax statuses may restrict transactions or require additional compliance checks   \n  - Occupation and employer details  \n  - Annual income band and source of funds\n\n- **Suitability profile data**  \n  - Investment experience (years, products used)   \n  - Any documented regulatory constraints (e.g., product restrictions, FATCA/CRS implications).\n\n### 2.2 Risk Profile Data\n\nRequired to ensure the retirement strategy and product choices are suitable:\n\n- Risk profile questionnaire responses  \n- Derived risk score/risk category (e.g., Conservative, Moderate, Aggressive)  \n- Time horizon preferences and capacity for loss  \n- Liquidity and income needs (e.g., comfort with market volatility vs. need for stable income)  \n- Date of last risk assessment and next review due\n\nThese are accessed and viewed from the customer dashboard/risk profile screens for planning.  \n\n### 2.3 Income and Expense Data\n\nTo determine investible surplus available for retirement savings:\n\n- **Income**  \n  - Salary and employment income  \n  - Business or professional income  \n  - Rental income  \n  - Investment income (interest, dividends)  \n  - Other recurring income (pensions, annuities, etc.)\n\n- **Expenses**  \n  - Fixed household expenses (housing, utilities, education, insurance premiums)  \n  - Discretionary expenses (travel, entertainment, lifestyle)  \n  - Existing EMIs or instalments (loans, credit cards)  \n\n- **Net surplus/deficit**  \n  - Monthly and annual surplus available for retirement investing.\n\n### 2.4 Assets and Liabilities\n\nTo understand the current net worth and existing retirement resources:\n\n- **Assets**  \n  - Bank deposits and cash balances  \n  - Mutual funds, equities, bonds, structured products, etc.  \n  - Retirement-specific accounts (e.g., pensions, provident funds)  \n  - Real estate (primary residence and investment properties)  \n  - Insurance policies with savings/investment components\n\n- **Liabilities**  \n  - Home loans, personal loans, vehicle loans  \n  - Credit card and other short-term debts  \n  - Any other obligations that impact investible surplus or retirement horizon\n\nExisting holdings and transactions can be viewed from the customer’s dashboard holdings and transactions views to avoid duplicate data capture. \n\n### 2.5 Retirement Goal and Planning Parameters\n\nSpecific data you must capture for each retirement plan/goal:\n\n- **Goal definition**  \n  - Goal type: Retirement  \n  - Plan type: set to Retirement Planning  \n  - Plan objective: Retirement \n\n- **Timeline**  \n  - Current age and desired retirement age  \n  - Planned contribution period (start/end dates)  \n  - Expected retirement duration (life expectancy or planning horizon)\n\n- **Target amounts**  \n  - Desired monthly/annual income in retirement (in today’s currency)  \n  - Any lump sum targets at retirement (e.g., to clear loans, purchase property)  \n  - Target corpus at retirement (if specified)\n\n- **Assumptions**  \n  - Expected inflation rate  \n  - Expected pre- and post-retirement investment returns (aligned with risk profile)  \n  - Tax assumptions on contributions and withdrawals  \n  - Currency for planning\n\n- **Constraints and preferences**  \n  - Liquidity needs near or after retirement  \n  - Product preferences/avoidances (e.g., no derivatives, ESG focus)  \n  - Legal/estate considerations that may influence structure.\n\n### 2.6 Product and Portfolio Data\n\nTo map the retirement strategy to concrete investments:\n\n- **Product eligibility and setup**  \n  - Products/securities flagged as available for Retirement Planning and Retirement objective in product/security maintenance so they may be used in retirement strategies. \n\n- **Current portfolio**  \n  - List of existing securities and model portfolios already linked to retirement goals (if any)  \n  - Asset allocation across major categories (equity, debt, alternatives, cash)  \n  - Product-level risk, liquidity, and tenure characteristics.\n\n### 2.7 Transaction and Order Data (for Implementation)\n\nWhen you convert the retirement plan into actual investments via the PMS application:\n\n- **Order basics**    \n  - Investment account(s) and settlement (funding) account(s)  \n  - Transaction type: Purchase, SIP, Switch, Redemption, SWP, STP, etc.  \n  - Security/product selected (must be active and enabled for the relevant plan type)  \n  - Order date/time and applicable cut-off times\n\n- **Amount/units**  \n  - Transaction amount or units entered per order line  \n  - For systematic plans (SIP/STP/SWP), instalment amount and number of instalments, ensuring they meet minimum instalment rules.\n\n- **Redemption-specific data and validation**  \n  - Chosen redemption mode: amount or units  \n  - Entered redemption amount or units (per folio/account)  \n  - Validation that only permitted fields are editable and that amount-only redemptions follow configured rules (e.g., amount validation only, multiple-of-1 units where applicable).  \n  - Application of business rules such as allowing only one folio to be redeemed per order in certain contexts, when those restrictions are configured.\n\n- **Order tracking**  \n  - Each order’s lifecycle status (Pending, Pending Approval, Authorized, Rejected, Expired, Executed, Settled) is tracked in the Order Book.   \n  - Use the Order Book and downloadable Order Book Report to monitor all orders related to the retirement plan and maintain a complete audit trail.  \n\n---\n\n## 3. Governance, Privacy, and Documentation\n\nWhile doing retirement planning, ensure the following controls are observed:\n\n1. **Data governance and privacy**  \n   - Use only authorised customer data from core onboarding/KYC, risk, and holdings systems.   \n   - Limit access to customer information based on user roles and mappings (e.g., RM visibility over mapped customers and orders in the Order Book).   \n   - Ensure sensitive data (KYC documents, income, tax status) is handled and stored according to prevailing privacy policies.\n\n2. **Process prerequisites**  \n   - Confirm key maintenance setups (risk profile questionnaire, model portfolios, product/security parameters, disclaimers) are in place before planning and order placement, so that recommendations and transactions are fully compliant. \n\n3. **Audit trail and records**  \n   - Maintain a full audit of the planning process, including captured goals, risk profiles, scenario assumptions, and plan versions, as part of the broader plan journey.   \n   - Retain records of orders executed to implement the plan (via the Order Book and related reports) and link them to the relevant retirement goal where supported.  \n\n4. **Customer disclosures and approvals**  \n   - Provide mandated disclaimers and risk disclosures associated with products and projections.   \n   - Record the customer’s acceptance of the retirement plan and of any recommended product transactions.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Practical Checklist for the RM/Planner\n\nUse this quick checklist when starting retirement planning for a customer:\n\n1. Onboarding/KYC complete and KYC status acceptable for transactions.  \n2. Risk profile captured, current, and consistent with intended strategy.  \n3. Income, expenses, and surplus clearly documented.  \n4. Full asset and liability inventory captured, including existing retirement assets.  \n5. Retirement goal set with: retirement age, target income/lump sum, assumptions, and constraints.  \n6. Products eligible for Retirement Planning/Retirement objective identified.  \n7. Gap analysis and scenarios run; strategy agreed internally.  \n8. Plan document generated and reviewed with customer; consent recorded.  \n9. Implementation orders placed with correct investment accounts, transaction type, amounts/units, and all validations passed.  \n10. Orders monitored via Order Book/Order Book Report; plan and portfolio reviewed periodically and updated as needed.\n	\N	{"v2_workflow":true,"mode":"balanced","model":"gpt-5.1","seed_node_names":["No. of Installments should be greater than or equal to SIP/STP/SWP Min. No of Installments","Obs 16","Amount redemption - Validate Amount only","Full redemption - No validation","Validate that it should be in multiples of 1","pass the “Y” Flag in close AC field","don’t send the amount/unit in outbound file/API","restriction in the order placement i.e. only one folio can be redeemed at a time","aggregated holdings value","Max Drawdown"],"seed_node_ids":["report:warning_display","aum:aggregated_holdings_value","compliance:restriction_order_placement_i_e_only_one_folio_can_be_redeemed_at_a_time","compliance:don_t_send_amount_unit_outbound_file","compliance:no_installments_should_be_greater_than_or_equal_to_sip_stp_swp_min_no_installments","compliance:amount_redemption_validate_amount_only","compliance:full_redemption_no_validation","aum:max_drawdown","compliance:obs_16","compliance:pass_y_flag_close_ac_field","compliance:validate_that_it_should_be_multiples_1"],"expanded_nodes":23,"expanded_edges":594,"kg_guided_queries":["[Focused Response Directive]\\n\\nPlease follow these instructions when answering:\\n• Answer ONLY the specific question asked - be precise and direct\\n• Include ONLY information that is immed