chieve a retirement financial goal. This module will allow clients (and their advisors) to create a personalized retirement plan and track progress over time.\\\\n\\\\n**Objectives:**\\\\n- Provide tools for clients to determine the savings required and investment strategy to retire with a desired income or corpus.\\\\n- Integrate existing client data (age, current assets, income) to pre-fill and inform plan calculations.\\\\n- Ensure the retirement plan aligns with the client's risk tolerance and investment preferences.\\\\n- Enable advisors and clients to collaborate on plan creation, adjustments, and ongoing monitoring to improve client engagement and goal attainment.\\\\n- Comply with all regulatory guidelines and industry standards for financial planning and advice.\\\\n\\\\n## Stakeholders\\\\n- **Clients/End Users:** Individuals using the application to plan their retirement goals. They input personal data and preferences and review plan outcomes.\\\\n- **Relationship Managers/Advisors:** Financial advisors who assist clients in creating and reviewing retirement plans. They need oversight features and possibly an approval workflow for plans before implementation.\\\\n- **Product/Portfolio Managers:** Professionals who define the investment products, model portfolios, and allocation strategies available for use in retirement planning.\\\\n- **Compliance Officers:** Ensure the retirement planning feature adheres to financial regulations and that the plan recommendations are suitable given the client’s profile.\\\\n- **IT/System Administrators:** Manage system configuration, data integrations (market data feeds, custodial data, etc.), and overall platform performance, security, and support for the new module.\\\\n\\\\n## Data Requirements\\\\nThe retirement planning module will require various data inputs and references:\\\\n- **Client Demographics:** Age, current age, planned retirement age, life expectancy (if used), and other personal details (marital status,