 Scheduled imports (daily/intraday) from:\n    - SFTP / shared folders  \n    - Email attachments  \n    - APIs / web services  \n  - Ensures latest external data is always available for reconciliation.\n\n- **Configurable mapping**\n  - Map external file fields to internal data fields.\n  - Supports common industry formats (RTA, custodian, bank files) and custom layouts.\n  - Handles differences in date formats, decimals, field names, and sign conventions.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Matching Logic and Rules\n\n- **Configurable matching rules**\n  - Separate rule sets for:\n    - Cash reconciliation\n    - Positions/holdings\n    - Trades and settlements\n  - Typical match keys: client/account, ISIN/security/fund code, transaction type, trade/settlement date, units/amount.\n\n- **Tolerance thresholds**\n  - Define acceptable variances for amounts/units (e.g., rounding differences).\n  - Classify as:\n    - Exact match\n    - Match within tolerance (variance highlighted)\n    - Break/exception (beyond tolerance)\n\n- **Auto‑matching engine**\n  - Automatically compares internal vs external records and categorizes:\n    - Fully matched\n    - Matched with variance (within tolerance)\n    - Unmatched internal items\n    - Unmatched external items\n\n---\n\n## 3. Exception Management and Workflow\n\n- **Exception queues**\n  - Central screen/dashboard listing:\n    - Unmatched items\n    - Partial/variance matches\n  - Side‑by‑side view of internal vs external details.\n\n- **User actions**\n  - **Manual match**: Link records the system could not auto‑match.\n  - **Accept with adjustment**:\n    - Handle partial fills/partial settlements.\n    - Split or adjust internal records (e.g., settled vs outstanding quantity).\n  - **Reject**:\n    - Mark irrelevant or erroneous external items.\n    - Capture reason/remarks.\n\n- **Real‑time updates**\n  - On acceptance, update:\n    - Order/trade status (e.g., confirmed/settled)\n    - Positions/holdings\n    - Cash balances and related bookkeeping entries.\n\n- **Remarks and categorization**\n  - Apply reason codes (e.g., “awaiting custodian clarification”).\n  - Store comments for future review and reporting.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Approvals and Audit Trail\n\n- **Approval workflows**\n  - Optional maker–checker for:\n    - Manual matches\n    - Adjustments\n    - Write‑offs beyond thresholds\n  - Supervisor/approver reviews and approves/rejects changes before they impact books.\n\n- **Audit trail**\n  - Logs for:\n    - Each reconciliation run\n    - Match/unmatch decisions\n    - Manual overrides and adjustments\n    - Approvals/rejections\n  - Captures user, timestamp, old vs new values, and comments.\n\n- **Versioning**\n  - Retains historical versions when records are updated (e.g., splitting a trade into settled and residual parts).\n  - Enables full reconstruction of reconciliation history.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Scheduling, Automation, and Alerts\n\n- **Scheduled runs**\n  - Configure daily, weekly, monthly, or custom schedules:\n    - Daily trade and cash reconciliation\n    - Periodic positions/holdings reconciliation\n\n- **Event‑driven triggers**\n  - Run reconciliation automatically when:\n    - New files arrive\n    - A trading day is closed\n    - Specific events occur in upstream systems\n\n- **Alerts and notifications**\n  - Notify users when:\n    - A scheduled run fails or data is missing\n    - Exception volumes exceed thresholds\n    - Items remain unresolved beyond defined aging limits\n  - Support email summaries and in‑app notifications.\n\n---\n\n## 6. Dashboards and Reporting\n\n- **Operational dashboards**\n  - High‑level status by module (cash, trades, positions, settlements):\n    - Total items vs matched vs exceptions\n    - Aging of breaks\n    - Trend of breaks over time\n\n- **Detailed reports**\n  - Exception reports with:\n    - Internal and external values\n    - Variances\n    - Reason codes and comments\n    - Action/approval history\n  - Filterable by date, account, fund, custodian, or source.\n\n- **Export and distribution**\n  - Export to Excel/PDF/CSV.\n  - Schedule automated distribution (e.g., daily reconciliation summary to Ops/Compliance).\n\n---\n\n## 7. Integration and Compliance\n\n- **Integration**\n  - Secure connectivity to RTAs, custodians, banks, PMS, and internal systems via:\n    - APIs\n    - Secure file transfer\n  - Post‑reconciliation updates can feed:\n    - Accounting/general ledger\n    - Risk and reporting systems\n    - Client reporting engines\n\n- **Controls and compliance**\n  - Regular reconciliations support:\n    - Accurate books and records\n    - Segregation of duties (maker–checker)\n    - Internal control and regulatory requirements (e.g., timely settlement, client asset protection).\n\n- **Audit and regulatory support**\n  - Provide regulators/auditors with:\n    - Historical reconciliation logs\n    - Exception and resolution history\n    - Evidence of periodic reconciliations and approvals.\n\n---\n\nIn summary, the product offers a configurable, automated reconciliation framework across cash, positions, trades, and settlements, with strong exception handling, approvals, auditability, and reporting tailored to wealth‑management operations.	{\n  "stepback_intent": "Provide a comprehensive overview of the product’s reconciliation capabilities for financial operations, covering how it ingests and matches data from external sources, handles exceptions (with approvals and audit trails), automates reconciliation processes, and offers reporting across various modules.",\n  "expanded_question": "What reconciliation features does the product offer across its various modules (cash, positions, trades, settlements)? In particular, how does it handle reconciliation workflows, data feed ingestion from external sources (such as RTA, custodian, or PMS feeds), matching logic with tolerance thresholds, exception management and approval processes, audit trails and versioning of changes, automated scheduling and al