ce approved, the system routes the order to the product processor for execution. This step connects the order from capture/approval to the execution layer. \n\n4) Trade Execution and File Generation\n- For mutual fund orders, a file is generated after approval and the system assigns an Order Reference Number (often sent to the relevant settlement processor). This file-based handoff enables downstream processing with custodians/RTAs. \n\n5) Settlement and Holdings Update\n- Settlement updates are performed after receiving the trade file from the settlement ecosystem. The process reconciles cash balances and customer holdings to reflect the executed trade. Settlement timing and the mechanics of updating holdings are defined in the journey flow.  \n\n6) NAV and Pricing Snapshots (Post-Trade Considerations)\n- During processing, indicative pricing and NAV-related data may be fetched and displayed (e.g., NAV Date, Net Investment Amount, Estimated Units, Indicative Price) to present the trade context to users and confirmations. These data points are surfaced as part of order details. \n\n7) Order Status, Audit, and UI/Workflow Components\n- User interfaces provide overlays and screens for reviewing Security Info, Order Info, and any Document Uploads. Orders progress through statuses (e.g., Pending Approval) and are viewable in an Order Book or equivalent dashboard. This lifecycle is reflected in typical mutual fund journeys and order-detail screens.  \n- The Product Cart consolidates multiple orders (grouped by transaction type) for review prior to submission, and is displayed on the Customer Dashboard. This UI pattern supports batch processing and visibility of orders before final submission. \n\n8) Transaction Types Supported\n- The platform supports common mutual fund transaction types such as Purchase, Redemption, Switch, and Systematic Plans (SIP, STP, SWP). The journey documents describe these transaction types and their routing/settlement flows.  \n\n9) Prerequisites and Compliance Context\n- Pre-requisites for the order journey include customer profile management, risk profiling, and maintenance workflows that ensure accurate and compliant order entry. These prerequisites are documented as part of the end-to-end journey and governance context. \n\nOverall, the mutual fund order processing flow follows a structured pattern: capture and submit the order, authorize/review, route for execution, generate the trade file and reference, settle and update holdings, and surface the process through clear UI screens and dashboards for monitoring and post-trade visibility. This lifecycle is consistently described across multiple journey documents, including those detailing end-to-end flows from order placement to settlement and the associated UI overlays. fileciteturn0file0turn0file15turn0file8turn0file9	\N	{"v2_workflow":true,"mode":"concise","model":"gpt-5-nano","seed_node_names":["Journey from Order Placement till Settlement","Order Book Report","Mutual Funds","Mutual Fund - Mode of Transaction","Mutual Fund - Input SWP Details","Product Cart","India Infoline Wealth","RTA Transaction File","SIP Scheduler","PRODUCT SELECTION SCREEN"],"seed_node_ids":["dataentity:product_cart","system:sip_scheduler","system:mutual_fund_input_swp_details","report:mutual_fund_input_sip_details","dataentity:transaction","datastore:rta_transaction_file","system:product_selection","report:order_book_report","datastore:product_cart","report:product_cart","system:product_cart","system:mutual_fund_mode_transaction","report:product_selection_screen","report:mutual_fund_mode_transaction","dataentity:mutual_funds","report:journey_from_order_placement_till_settlement","dataentity:warning_message","system:india_infoline_wealth"],"expanded_nodes":71,"expanded_edges":123,"kg_guided_queries":["Previous context ID: 246ffa8a-4ee3-4099-aebb-1241f8307b64\\n\\nQuestion: [Context-Aware Follow-up Question with Focus Directives]\\n\\nPrevious conversation history is prov