nning workflows. These data points guide the planning assumptions and target outcomes. - Planning typically begins with defining objectives and the relevant plan type (e.g., Wealth Planning, Retirement Planning, Education Planning, Tax Planning, Execution Planning). ## Modeling approaches and planning components - Asset allocation is a core component of the modeling process, with detailed sub-allocations and security-level considerations as part of Model Portfolio configuration. - Model Portfolio concepts underpin the planning process: the portfolio mix is defined for each risk profile, and is maintained/adjusted through a formal model-portfolio workflow. - Outputs include model portfolio structures and related compositions (asset class, sector, and security allocations) that form the basis of recommendations. - In some implementations, the platform provides projections and performance views (e.g., projection scenarios, back-testing visuals, and risk-adjusted metrics) as part of the planning and monitoring process. ## End-to-end workflow and governance - Planning is guided by a defined Plan Journey for Financial Goals and Investments, outlining the sequence from goals definition to investment initiation. - Planning involves explicit authorizations and approvals before execution, ensuring governance and risk controls are applied (e.g., supervisor approvals and risk-deviation handling). - The Model Portfolio workflow includes steps such as asset allocation, sub-asset allocation, security portfolio setup, and model portfolio creation, with defined prerequisites and authorization points. ## Deliverables and client-facing outputs - The platform produces model portfolio-related outputs and reports that summarize the investment strategy aligned to the client’s risk profile and planning objectives. These include model portfolio details and related compositions (Asset Class, Sector, Securities). - Portfolio selections and overlays feed into the broader client-facing dashboards (e.g., client dashboard views that expose risk, goals, holdings, and plan progress). - In practice, planned actions are translated into orders and transactions within the system (e.g., order capture, authorization, routing, and settlement) to implement the plan. This flow is governed by authorization steps and is reflected in the order lifecycle. ## Notes on risk and monitoring - Risk profiling and monitoring are integral to the planning process, with risk-profile-based planning and ongoing risk deviation alerts in the workflow. - Projections and risk metrics (e.g., scenarios and max-drawdown visuals) provide the analytical backbone for sensitivity testing and plan validation.	\N	{"v2_workflow":true,"mode":"concise","model":"gpt-5-nano","seed_node_names":["Risk Profile Questionnaire","Customer Risk profile","Model Portfolio – Order Placement","Model Portfolio - Composition","Mutual Funds","Mutual Fund – Product Selection","Product Selection – Overlay","Customer Dashboard","Order Book Report","Screen: Model Portfolio – Selection"],"seed_node_ids":["dataentity:customer","report:model_pf_order_placement","system:product_selection","dataentity:mutual_funds","report:product_selection_overlay","report:model_pf_composition","report:screen_model_pf_selection","dataentity:product_selection_overlay","aum:customer_risk_profile","report:order_book_report","dataentity:risk_profile_questionnaire","report:risk_profile_questionnaire","report:customer_dashboard","report:mutual_fund_product_selection"],"expanded_nodes":51,"expanded_edges":78,"kg_guided_queries":["Previous context ID: 3d6dbd0b-5f44-4924-bb4e-444320f03076\\n\\nQuestion: [Context-Aware Follow-up Question with Focus Directives]\\n\\nPrevious conversation history is provided for context. Please follow these instructions:\\n\\nSTEP 1 - Context Understanding:\\n• Evaluate if this question contains pronouns or unclear references (e.g., \\"this\\", \\"it\\", \\"that\\", \\"these\\", \\"the above\\")\\n• If such references 