**\n- **Investors (Clients):** Use web/mobile to set up retirement goals, choose contributions, and monitor progress.\n- **Relationship Managers (RMs) / Advisors:** Create and manage plans for/with clients, explain scenarios, ensure suitability.\n\n**Secondary:**\n- **Operations & Back Office:** Handle transaction processing, folio creation, reconciliations.\n- **Compliance & Risk:** Ensure adherence to KYC, suitability, and nomination rules.\n- **Product Management:** Owns feature roadmap and business outcomes.\n- **IT / Support:** Develops, maintains, and supports the solution.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Data Requirements & Model\n\n**Key entities:**\n- **Investor Profile**\n  - Demographics: age, gender, residency.\n  - Financials: income, existing assets, liabilities.\n  - KYC status (e.g., KYC Registered).\n  - Risk profile (score, category, last assessment date).\n\n- **Retirement Goal**\n  - Goal ID, Investor ID.\n  - Goal type = `Retirement`.\n  - Target retirement age/date.\n  - Target corpus (in current or future value).\n  - Assumptions: expected return, inflation, contribution escalation.\n  - Status: Draft, Active, On-track, Off-track, Achieved, Closed.\n\n- **Investment Products**\n  - Product master: ISIN, fund code, name, asset class.\n  - Risk rating.\n  - Eligibility flags (e.g., “Retirement eligible”).\n  - Transaction rules: min/max SIP & lump sum, allowed frequencies, cut-off times, SIP/SWP support.\n\n- **Accounts / Folios**\n  - Account/folio ID, investor ID.\n  - Product/fund mapping.\n  - Nomination status: Nominee present / Opted-out.\n  - Bank mandate details (for SIP/SWP).\n\n- **Transactions**\n  - Orders: purchase, SIP, switch, redemption, SWP.\n  - Status: Draft, Pending, Rejected, Executed, Cancelled.\n  - Goal tag (linking each transaction to the retirement goal).\n\n- **Market & Reference Data**\n  - Daily NAVs, prices.\n  - Product risk ratings, categories.\n  - Calendar/business days, cut-off times.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Regulatory & Compliance\n\n**Requirements:**\n- **KYC:** No investment orders allowed without completed KYC.\n- **Suitability:**\n  - Valid risk profile required before plan activation.\n  - Product risk vs. client risk profile checks:\n    - Soft warning for mild mismatches (with explicit acknowledgement).\n    - Hard block for severe mismatches unless approved override.\n- **Nomination:**\n  - For new folios, capture either nominee details or explicit opt-out declaration.\n  - Block order submission if neither is provided.\n- **Disclosures:**\n  - Clear disclaimers that projections are estimates, not guarantees.\n  - Display assumptions used in calculations.\n- **Audit Trail:**\n  - Log goal creation, changes, orders, overrides, and client declarations.\n  - Retain evidence of nomination opt-out and suitability overrides.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Integration Points\n\n- **CRM:**\n  - Pull investor profile, risk scores, and life events.\n  - Push goal metadata (e.g., presence of retirement goal) for RM dashboards.\n\n- **Custodian / RTA (e.g., CAMS):**\n  - Send purchase/SIP/SWP/switch orders.\n  - Receive confirmations, folio numbers, and unit allocations.\n  - Maintain consistent goal tags on transactions where supported.\n\n- **Financial Planning / Calculation Engine:**\n  - Perform projections (FV, PV, SIP calculations; optionally scenario analysis).\n  - Expose APIs for real-time recalculation as inputs change.\n\n- **Market Data Feeds:**\n  - NAVs and product reference data for accurate valuations and projections.\n\n- **Notification Services:**\n  - Email/SMS/in-app alerts for:\n    - Plan creation/activation.\n    - Order confirmations/failures.\n    - Upcoming SIP/SWP dates.\n    - Goal off-track alerts.\n    - Approaching retirement date.\n\n---\n\n## 6. Functional Requirements\n\n### 6.1 Goal Setup & Definition\n- Create a new goal with:\n  - Target retirement age/date.\n  - Target corpus (optionally: desired monthly income in retirement).\n  - Current savings earmarked for retirement.\n  - Assumptions: expected return, inflation, contribution escalation.\n- Validate:\n  - Age and retirement age are logical (e.g., retirement age > current age).\n  - Target amount > 0.\n- Save as Draft or proceed to recommendation.\n\n### 6.2 Plan Recommendation\n- Use risk profile and time horizon to:\n  - Suggest asset allocation (e.g., equity vs. debt).\n  - Map to model portfolios or recommended fund baskets.\n- Show:\n  - Recommended products and allocation.\n  - Projected corpus vs. target.\n  - Probability or range of outcomes (if supported).\n\n### 6.3 Product Selection\n- Display recommended products with:\n  - Name, category, risk rating, key metrics.\n- Allow:\n  - Accepting recommended set as-is.\n  - Limited customization (add/remove/replace) within suitability rules.\n- Enforce:\n  - Product eligibility (retirement-eligible, risk-compatible).\n  - Switch-in options only from valid funds when rebalancing.\n\n### 6.4 Contribution Planning (SIP / Lump Sum)\n- Allow:\n  - Initial lump sum.\n  - Recurring SIP (monthly/quarterly/etc.).\n  - Combination of both.\n- Provide calculators:\n  - Given contribution → projected corpus.\n  - Given target corpus → required contribution.\n- Validate:\n  - Against product min/max SIP and lump sum limits.\n  - Against allowed SIP dates and frequencies.\n\n### 6.5 Order Placement & Execution\n- Generate:\n  - Purchase orders for lump sum.\n  - SIP instructions for recurring contributions.\n- Present consolidated order summary (“cart”) with:\n  - Funds, amounts, folios, SIP dates.\n- Support:\n  - OTP or equivalent strong customer authentication.\n- Submit orders to standard order-processing workflow and update statuses.\n\n### 6.6 Drafts & Pending Orders\n- Allow saving:\n  - Draft goals (no orders yet).\n  - Draft orders (unsubmitted).\n- Provide:\n  - “Pending” bucket for RMs/clients to resume and submit later.\n\n### 6.7 Order Lifecycle & Tracking\n- Show:\n  - Orders in Order Book with real-time status.\n  - Execution details and allocated units once confirmed by RTA.\n- Tag:\n  - All relevant orders and holdings with the retirement goal for reporting.\n\n### 6.8 Goal Monitoring & Progress\n- Dashboard:\n  - Current value vs. target.\n  - % of goal achieved.\n  - Projected outcome vs. target.\n- Detailed view:\n  - Contribution history.\n  - Performance metrics.\n  - Projection charts.\n- Alerts:\n  - Off-track status based on configurable thresholds.\n\n### 6.9 Plan Adjustments\n- Allow changes to:\n  - Target amount/date.\n  - Contribution amount/frequency.\n  - Product mix (rebalancing, switches).\n- Trigger:\n  - Recalculation of projections.\n  - Suitability checks on new products.\n- Log:\n  - All changes with timestamps and user IDs.\n\n### 6.10 Retirement & Withdrawal Phase\n- At/near retirement:\n  - Allow conversion from accumulation to distribution strategy.\n- Support:\n  - SWP setup (amount or % and frequency).\n  - One-time redemptions.\n- Validate:\n  - SWP feasibility vs. holdings and product rules.\n- Track:\n  - SWP instructions and redemptions under the retirement goal.\n\n---\n\n## 7. Non-Functional Requirements\n\n**Performance**\n- Projection and recalculation responses within a few seconds under normal load.\n- Order submission and status updates within existing platform SLAs.\n\n**Scalability**\n- Support large volumes of goals and transactions.\n- Horizontally scalable services for calculations and reporting.\n\n**Security**\n- Encryption in transit and at rest.\n- Role-based access control:\n  - Clients: own data only.\n  - RMs: assigned clients only.\n- Full audit logging of access and changes.\n\n**Availability & Reliability**\n- High availability consistent with core wealth platform.\n- Graceful degradation and retries for calculation or integration failures.\n\n**Audit & Monitoring**\n- Centralized logging for:\n  - Goal lifecycle events.\n  - Order events.\n  - Integration errors.\n- Dashboards and alerts for:\n  - Latency, error rates, failed integrations.\n\n**Usability & Accessibility**\n- Intuitive, guided flows (wizard-style).\n- Clear labels, tooltips, and inline help.\n- Responsive design for web and mobile.\n- Accessibility support (screen readers, keyboard navigation).\n\n---\n\n## 8. Reporting & Analytics\n\n**Client-Facing:**\n- Retirement Plan Summary:\n  - Goal parameters, contributions, current value, projected value.\n- Goal-specific Order Report:\n  - All transactions tagged to the retirement goal for a selected period.\n- Export to PDF/Excel.\n\n**RM / Advisory:**\n- Client lists:\n  - Clients with/without retirement goals.\n  - Clients off-track or underfunded.\n- Activity:\n  - Number of plans created, modified, or closed.\n\n**Management / MIS:**\n- Adoption metrics:\n  - Plans created, active, and funded.\n- AUM:\n  - Assets under retirement goals vs. total AUM.\n- Product usage within retirement plans.\n\n**Regulatory:**\n- Nomination status reports for new folios.\n- Suitability override logs.\n- Evidence of disclosures and assumptions used.\n\n---\n\n## 9. UI / UX Considerations\n\n**Entry Points:**\n- Main navigation: “Goals” → “Retirement”.\n- Dashboard widget: “Plan Your Retirement” / “Retirement Goal”.\n\n**Goal Setup Wizard:**\n1. Personal & basic info (age, retirement age, current savings).\n2. Target corpus / desired retirement income.\n3. Recommended plan & projections.\n4. Product selection & contribution setup.\n5. Review & confirm.\n\n**Product & Summary Screens:**\n- Clear list of recommended funds with key attributes.\n- Filters and warnings for risk mismatches.\n- Single summary page before confirmation.\n\n**Visualizations:**\n- Projection chart (current vs. target over time).\n- Progress bar (% of goal achieved).\n- Contribution and performance charts.\n\n**Mobile:**\n- Optimized layouts for small screens.\n- Simplified charts and calculators.\n\n**Error Handling & Help:**\n- Field-level validation messages.\n- Tooltips for financial terms.\n- Links to FAQs or help center.\n\n---\n\n## 10. Validation Rules\n\n- **Mandatory Fields:**\n  - Target retirement age/date, target corpus, contribution details, nominee/opt-out.\n- **KYC & Risk Profile:**\n  - Block investments if KYC incomplete.\n  - Block or redirect to risk profiling if no valid risk profile.\n- **Suitability:**\n  - Compare product risk vs. client risk.\n  - Soft/hard rules as per policy.\n- **Nomination:**\n  - Require full nominee details or explicit opt-out confirmation for new folios.\n- **Transaction Limits:**\n  - Enforce product-level min/max for SIP and lump sum.\n  - Additional checks for very large amounts (e.g., manual review).\n- **Schedule Constraints:**\n  - Only allow SIP/SWP dates and frequencies supported by each product.\n- **Cut-off Times:**\n  - Orders after cut-off queued for next business day.\n  - Inform client of applicable trade date.\n\n---\n\n## 11. Acceptance Criteria (High-Level)\n\n- A client with valid KYC and risk profile can:\n  - Create and save a retirement goal.\n  - Receive a recommended plan.\n  - Select products within suitability rules.\n  - Set up SIP/lump sum contributions.\n  - Successfully place orders and see them in the Order Book.\n\n- System:\n  - Blocks investments for non-KYC or missing risk profile.\n  - Enforces nomination rules for new folios.\n  - Applies product-level limits and schedule constraints.\n  - Correctly tags and reports all goal-related transactions.\n  - Updates goal progress and projections after market or contribution changes.\n\n---\n\n## 12. Implementation Timeline (Indicative)\n\n- **Phase 1 (3–4 months):**\n  - Core goal setup, projections, product selection, and transaction integration.\n  - Basic dashboard and reporting.\n  - UAT with internal users and selected RMs.\n\n- **Phase 2 (2–3 months):**\n  - Advanced analytics and scenario analysis.\n  - Enhanced visualizations and UX refinements.\n  - Performance tuning and security hardening.\n\n- **Phase 3 (≈1 month):**\n  - Full rollout to all clients and RMs.\n  - Training, documentation, and marketing.\n  - Post-launch monitoring and minor enhancements.\n\nTimelines assume existing CRM, RTA, and market data integrations are available and stable.\n\n---\n\n## 13. Governance\n\n- **Steering Committee:**\n  - Product, IT, Compliance, Advisory.\n  - Approves scope, timelines, and go-live decisions.\n\n- **Project Team:**\n  - BA: Owns requirements and traceability.\n  - PM: Manages delivery, dependencies, and communication.\n  - Tech Leads: Own design and implementation.\n  - QA: Owns test strategy and execution.\n\n- **Change Control:**\n  - Formal process for requirement changes with impact analysis and approvals.\n\n- **Post-Launch Ownership:**\n  - Product: Business KPIs and roadmap.\n  - IT: Operations, SLAs, incident management.\n\n---\n\n## 14. Risks & Assumptions\n\n**Assumptions:**\n- Accurate and timely data from CRM, product master, and market feeds.\n- RTA/custodian APIs support required fields and volumes.\n- Regulatory environment remains broadly stable during build.\n\n**Key Risks & Mitigations:**\n- **Integration Delays:**  \n  - Mitigation: Early engagement, mock interfaces, phased rollout.\n- **Regulatory Changes Mid-Project:**  \n  - Mitigation: Continuous involvement of Compliance; buffer in plan.\n- **Low Adoption by RMs/Clients:**  \n  - Mitigation: Training, simple UX, and internal promotion.\n- **Projection Misinterpretation:**  \n  - Mitigation: Conservative defaults, clear disclosures, scenario ranges.\n- **Data Privacy/Security Incidents:**  \n  - Mitigation: Strong security controls, monitoring, and incident response plan.\n\nA living risk log will be maintained with owners, impact, and mitigation actions.\n\n---\n\nThis BRD defines the business requirements for implementing a comprehensive Retirement Planning capability within the wealth management platform, covering scope, functionality, integrations, compliance, and delivery approach.	{\n  "stepback_intent": "Prepare a comprehensive Business Requirements Document for implementing a retirement planning feature in a wealth management platform.",\n  "expanded_question": "How can we develop a detailed BRD for a Retirement Planning capability in our wealth management platform, covering its scope, objectives, stakeholders (investors, advisors), data requirements and model, regulatory and compliance needs, integration with systems (CRM, custodian APIs, planning tools), user personas, functional and non-functional requirements, UI/UX design, reporting, validation rules, acceptance criteria, implementation timeline, governance, and risk/assumptions?",\n  "business_entities": ["Investor", "Risk profiling", "Product risk profile", "Opting out of nomination", "Switch-In Fund Dropdown", "Order Book Report", "Order(s) in Pending State bucket", "Product Selection Screen", "SIP", "Mutual Funds", "CAMS"],\n  "citations": [\n    {"id": "1", "source": "JBR_Journey from Order Placement till Settlement - G073 Part A and Part B - Basket based order trigger (1).pdf"},\n    {"id": "2", "source": "SBI_Journey of Defining Maintenances__V10.pdf"},\n    {"id": "3", "source": "JBR_Journey of Creating Model Portfolio_V1_CCV1.pdf"},\n    {"id": "4", "source": "JioBlackRock_Journey of Self Assessment and Supervisor Assessment - RM Dashboard_V10_CCV10.pdf"},\n    {"id": "5", "source": "SBI_Journey from Order Placement till Settlement_New SEBI Regulation_V13.pdf"},\n    {"id": "6", "source": "HSBC_Journey from Order Placement till Settlement_V11_CCV10_Part 2.pdf"},\n    {"id": "8", "source": "360ONE_Journey from Order Placement till Settlement_V11_CCV13_Part 3.pdf"},\n    {"id": "9", "source": "SBI International_Journey of Launching a New Product_V10.pdf"},\n    {"id": "10", "source": "SBI_Journey from Order Placement till Settlement_G27_G28_SIP SWP STP.pdf"},\n    {"id": "11", "source": "SBI_Journey from Order Placement till Settlement_SEBI Nominee changes Phase 1_V10.pdf"},\n    {"id": "12", "source": "SBI_Journey of Launch