:\n\n- Provide a structured, compliant, and repeatable retirement planning process.\n- Ensure recommendations are suitable for the client’s risk profile and time horizon.\n- Integrate planning with order execution and ongoing goal tracking.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Scope\n\n**In Scope**\n\n- Capture and maintain retirement-specific goal data.\n- Use client profile, KYC, and risk profile as inputs.\n- Calculate required contributions (SIP/lump sum) and projections.\n- Recommend asset allocation and (optionally) products.\n- Scenario analysis (optimistic/base/pessimistic).\n- Workflow: advisor creation → supervisor approval → client acceptance → execution.\n- Integration with order placement, pricing, and client dashboards.\n- Compliance checks (KYC, suitability, maker-checker, audit trail).\n- Reporting: plan report, progress dashboard, review reports.\n\n**Out of Scope (for now)**\n\n- Tax optimization engine.\n- Complex estate planning.\n- Cross-border retirement rules.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Stakeholders\n\n- **Client (Investor)** – Provides inputs, reviews and accepts the plan, funds investments, monitors progress.\n- **Advisor / Relationship Manager** – Gathers data, creates and explains the plan, initiates investments, reviews periodically.\n- **Supervisor / Compliance Officer** – Reviews and approves plans, ensures suitability and regulatory compliance.\n- **Operations / IT** – Manages integrations, data quality, performance, security, and support.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Key Business Entities\n\n- **Client** (and related accounts).\n- **Retirement Goal** (goal master record).\n- **Risk Profile** (score, category, validity).\n- **Model Portfolio / Strategy** (by risk and goal type).\n- **Investment Orders** (lump sum, SIP, SWP).\n- **Plan Version / Scenario** (baseline, optimistic, pessimistic).\n\n---\n\n## 5. Client Profile & Data Requirements\n\nThe module must use and/or capture:\n\n- **Personal details**: age, current age, planned retirement age, marital status, dependents.\n- **Financials**:\n  - Income and expenses.\n  - Existing assets (investments, retirement accounts, pensions).\n  - Liabilities (loans, obligations).\n- **Regulatory status**:\n  - KYC status (must be valid before execution).\n  - Risk profile (score, category such as Conservative/Moderate/Aggressive, and validity date).\n- **Retirement-specific inputs**:\n  - Target retirement age/date.\n  - Desired retirement income and/or target corpus.\n  - Current savings earmarked for retirement.\n  - Assumed life expectancy / planning horizon post-retirement.\n  - Contribution capacity (max monthly/annual contribution).\n\n**Business rules**\n\n- Retirement age must be > current age.\n- Life expectancy must be within a reasonable range (configurable).\n- Mandatory fields must be completed before calculations.\n- If risk profile is missing or expired, advisor must complete/refresh it before proceeding to plan or orders.\n\n---\n\n## 6. Retirement Goal Definition\n\nThe system will provide a **Retirement Goal Definition** screen to capture:\n\n- Goal name (e.g., “Retirement – Self”, “Retirement – Spouse”).\n- Goal type: **Retirement** (distinct from other goal types).\n- Target retirement age/date.\n- Target:\n  - Monthly/annual income in retirement, and/or\n  - Total corpus required at retirement.\n- Current retirement savings (EPF, NPS, pensions, investments already earmarked).\n- Time horizon:\n  - Accumulation period (now → retirement).\n  - Retirement period (retirement → life expectancy).\n- Assumptions:\n  - Inflation (pre- and post-retirement).\n  - Expected returns by asset class or portfolio.\n- Contribution constraints:\n  - Max affordable monthly/annual contribution.\n  - Existing SIPs that can be mapped to this goal.\n\nThe goal record must be:\n\n- Linked to the client and relevant accounts.\n- Classified as “Retirement” for reporting and filtering.\n- Able to be versioned (e.g., revised goal parameters over time).\n\n---\n\n## 7. Calculations & Projections\n\n### 7.1 Required Contribution\n\nThe system must:\n\n- Calculate required **monthly/annual contribution** to reach the target corpus, given:\n  - Current savings.\n  - Time to retirement.\n  - Expected return assumptions.\n- Support:\n  - SIP-style periodic contribution calculator.\n  - Lump-sum growth calculator (how a one-time investment grows to retirement).\n- Allow reverse calculations:\n  - Given a fixed monthly contribution, compute achievable corpus.\n\n### 7.2 Asset Allocation Strategy\n\n- Use **risk profile** and **time horizon** to propose an asset allocation (e.g., equity, debt, cash).\n- Support:\n  - Predefined **model portfolios** by risk category and goal type (e.g., “Retirement – Moderate”).\n  - Custom allocation (with validation that total = 100%).\n- Enforce:\n  - Recommended allocation must not exceed client’s risk category.\n  - As retirement nears, allocation should be capable of being shifted to more conservative mix (configurable glide path, if implemented).\n\n### 7.3 Growth & Withdrawal Projections\n\n- Generate projections from current date to:\n  - Retirement date (accumulation phase).\n  - End of retirement horizon (withdrawal phase, if modeled).\n- Show:\n  - Year-by-year (or configurable period) projected portfolio value.\n  - Contributions vs. investment growth components.\n- Support **Systematic Withdrawal Plan (SWP)** modeling:\n  - Given corpus and withdrawal amount, estimate duration.\n  - Or given desired duration, estimate required corpus.\n\n### 7.4 Scenario Analysis\n\n- Allow multiple scenarios per goal:\n  - Baseline (default assumptions).\n  - Optimistic (higher returns / lower inflation).\n  - Pessimistic (lower returns / higher inflation).\n- Show side-by-side comparison:\n  - Projected corpus at retirement.\n  - Probability of shortfall (if supported by analytics).\n- Allow quick adjustment of key assumptions with instant recalculation.\n\n### 7.5 Metrics\n\n- Display key metrics:\n  - Target vs. projected corpus.\n  - Shortfall/surplus at retirement.\n  - Goal achievement probability (if available).\n  - Expected portfolio return (and basic risk indicators if available).\n\n---\n\n## 8. User Interface Requirements\n\n### 8.1 Entry Points\n\n- From **Client Profile / Dashboard**:\n  - “Create Retirement Plan” or “Add Retirement Goal”.\n- From **Goals section**:\n  - List of goals including Retirement; ability to view/edit.\n\n### 8.2 Goal Definition Screen\n\n- Form-based UI with:\n  - Client and goal identifiers.\n  - Fields for target age/date, income/corpus, current savings, assumptions.\n  - Validations and inline help.\n- Actions:\n  - Save as Draft.\n  - Run Calculations.\n  - Create additional scenarios.\n\n### 8.3 Planning Results & Scenario Screen\n\n- Charts and tables showing:\n  - Projected portfolio value over time.\n  - Contributions vs. growth.\n  - Goal achievement percentage.\n- Scenario toggles (baseline/optimistic/pessimistic).\n- Ability to adjust assumptions and see live updates.\n\n### 8.4 Product Recommendation / Allocation Screen\n\n- Show recommended asset allocation and (optionally) product list:\n  - Asset class weights.\n  - Suggested funds/securities with risk rating and basic info.\n- Allow:\n  - Advisor adjustments within risk limits.\n  - Clear indication that this is a **Retirement** strategy.\n\n### 8.5 Workflow & Approval Screens\n\n- Advisor view:\n  - Plan status (Draft, Pending Approval, Approved, Active, Rejected).\n  - Submit for Approval button.\n- Supervisor view:\n  - Queue of plans pending approval.\n  - Full plan details and compliance flags.\n  - Approve / Reject / Return with comments.\n\n### 8.6 Client Presentation & Dashboard\n\n- **Retirement Plan Report** (on-screen and PDF):\n  - Goal summary, assumptions, contributions, allocation, projections, disclaimers.\n- **Goal Dashboard**:\n  - Retirement goal tile with:\n    - Target amount.\n    - Current value.\n    - % achieved.\n  - Drill-down to:\n    - Holdings mapped to the retirement goal.\n    - Updated projections vs. original plan.\n\n### 8.7 Order Placement Integration\n\n- From an approved plan:\n  - “Implement Plan” / “Invest Now” button.\n- Pre-populate:\n  - Securities/funds, amounts, accounts, SIP parameters.\n- Hand off to existing order journey:\n  - Confirm, submit, track status.\n- Tag all orders with the retirement goal ID for tracking.\n\n---\n\n## 9. Data Flows & Integrations\n\n- **Client & Account Master**:\n  - Read client details, KYC status, risk profile, accounts.\n- **Risk Profiling Service**:\n  - Fetch/create/update risk profile.\n- **Product & Pricing Data**:\n  - Read product master (funds, risk ratings, min amounts).\n  - Read pricing/NAV data for projections and order placement.\n- **Order Management / Execution**:\n  - Create and submit orders (lump sum, SIP, SWP).\n  - Receive execution status and confirmations.\n- **Analytics Engine** (optional/advanced):\n  - Monte Carlo or other risk analytics for probability-based projections.\n- **Reporting & Document Service**:\n  - Generate PDF reports and store them.\n\n---\n\n## 10. Compliance & Controls\n\nThe module must support:\n\n- **KYC Enforcement**\n  - No investment orders if KYC is not valid.\n- **Suitability**\n  - Risk profile must be present and valid.\n  - Product risk rating must not exceed client’s risk category (hard stop or configurable).\n  - Product time horizon / lock-in must be compatible with goal horizon (warnings or blocks).\n- **Maker-Checker**\n  - Advisor (maker) cannot implement plan until supervisor (checker) approves.\n  - Approval workflow configurable by role and thresholds.\n- **Audit Trail**\n  - Log all key actions:\n    - Plan creation, edits, approvals, rejections.\n    - Assumption changes.\n    - Order creation and execution.\n- **Disclosures & Disclaimers**\n  - All client-facing outputs must include:\n    - Market risk disclaimers.\n    - Statement that projections are estimates, not guarantees.\n    - Any required regulatory language.\n\n---\n\n## 11. Reporting & Outputs\n\n- **Retirement Plan Report (Client-facing)**\n  - Executive summary.\n  - Client and goal details.\n  - Assumptions.\n  - Contribution schedule.\n  - Asset allocation.\n  - Projections and charts.\n  - Shortfall/surplus analysis.\n  - Disclaimers.\n\n- **Goal Progress Dashboard**\n  - Current value vs. target.\n  - % achieved.\n  - On-track / off-track indicator.\n  - Holdings by goal.\n\n- **Periodic Review Report**\n  - Original vs. actual performance.\n  - Impact of deviations.\n  - Recommended adjustments (e.g., increase contributions).\n\n- **Internal/Compliance Reports**\n  - List of retirement plans by period, status, risk category.\n  - Exceptions (e.g., plans with overridden suitability warnings).\n  - Audit extracts for regulators.\n\n---\n\n## 12. Data Governance & Security\n\n- **Validation**\n  - Mandatory fields enforced.\n  - Logical checks (dates, ages, non-negative amounts).\n  - Allocation totals must sum to 100%.\n- **Consistency**\n  - Single source of truth for client, product, and pricing data.\n  - Store assumptions and results to reproduce historical plans.\n  - Versioning of plans and scenarios.\n- **Security & Privacy**\n  - Role-based access control (only assigned advisors/supervisors see a client’s plan).\n  - Encryption of sensitive data at rest and in transit.\n- **Retention**\n  - Retain plan and related order data for regulatory minimum periods.\n\n---\n\n## 13. End-to-End Workflow\n\n1. **Initiation**\n   - Advisor selects client and opens Retirement Planning.\n   - System checks KYC and risk profile; prompts completion if missing/expired.\n\n2. **Goal Setup**\n   - Advisor enters retirement goal details and assumptions.\n   - System validates and saves as Draft.\n\n3. **Plan Development**\n   - System calculates required contributions, allocation, and projections.\n   - Advisor reviews, adjusts assumptions/products, and creates scenarios.\n\n4. **Client Discussion**\n   - Advisor presents plan (on-screen or via report).\n   - Adjustments made as needed; plan re-run.\n\n5. **Internal Approval**\n   - Advisor submits plan for supervisor approval.\n   - Supervisor reviews, approves, or returns with comments.\n\n6. **Client Acceptance**\n   - Advisor presents approved plan to client.\n   - Client acceptance recorded (e.g., digital consent or documented confirmation).\n\n7. **Execution**\n   - Advisor triggers “Implement Plan”.\n   - Orders are created and submitted; status tracked.\n   - Goal is marked as Active and funded percentage updated.\n\n8. **Ongoing Monitoring & Review**\n   - Dashboard shows progress.\n   - Alerts for off-track goals or risk drift.\n   - Periodic review and plan revisions (with re-approval if material changes).\n\n---\n\n## 14. Acceptance Criteria\n\nThe Retirement Planning module will be considered accepted when:\n\n1. **Functional**\n   - All required data fields and validations work as specified.\n   - Calculations (SIP, lump sum, projections) are accurate within agreed tolerances.\n   - Asset allocation respects risk profile and time horizon rules.\n   - Scenario analysis works with instant recalculation.\n\n2. **Workflow**\n   - Advisor → Supervisor → Client → Execution flow works end-to-end.\n   - Maker-checker rules are enforced and configurable.\n   - Plan status transitions (Draft, Pending Approval, Approved, Active, Rejected) behave correctly.\n\n3. **Integration**\n   - Client, product, pricing, and order systems integrate without data loss or mismatch.\n   - Orders created from plans carry correct details and are executed successfully.\n   - Execution status updates the goal’s funded status.\n\n4. **Usability**\n   - Advisors can complete a typical plan within a reasonable time.\n   - UI is intuitive and consistent with existing platform standards.\n   - Reports generate correctly and are readable by clients.\n\n5. **Compliance & Audit**\n   - KYC and suitability checks prevent non-compliant actions.\n   - Audit logs capture all required events.\n   - Compliance team signs off that regulatory requirements are met.\n\n6. **Performance & Security**\n   - Projections for long horizons (e.g., 30+ years) run within acceptable response times.\n   - System supports concurrent users without significant degradation.\n   - Security controls (access, encryption) pass penetration and vulnerability tests.\n\n---\n\nThis BRD defines the business requirements for implementing a robust, compliant, and user-friendly **Retirement Planning** capability within a wealth management platform.	{\n  "stepback_intent": "Provide a comprehensive outline of business requirements for a Retirement Planning module in a wealth management platform.",\n  "expanded_question": "What are the detailed business requirements for adding a Retirement Planning module to our wealth management platform, covering scope, stakeholders, data model (client info, retirement goals), processes (goal setting, risk profiling, contribution planning), data flows, UI screens, compliance controls (KYC, suitability per SEBI), outputs (projections, dashboards), workflow (advisor/client/supervisor steps), integrations (fund data, pricing), and acceptance criteria?",\n  "business_entities": [\n    "Client (Investor)",\n    "Advisor (Relationship Manager)",\n    "Retirement Goal",\n    "Risk Profile",\n    "Model Portfolio",\n    "Investment Order"\n  ],\n  "citations": [\n    {"id": "1", "source": "Journey from Order Placement till Settlement – Basket Based Order Trigger (Jio/Intellect)"},\n    {"id": "2", "source": "Journey of Creating Model Portfolio (SBI)"},\n    {"id": "3", "source": "Journey from Order Placement till Settlement (HSBC)"},\n    {"id": "4", "source": "Journey from Order Placement till Settlement (360One)"},\n    {"id": "5", "source": "Journey from Order Placement till Settlement (SBI)"},\n    {"id": "6", "source": "Model Portfolio/Basket Based Investments (Product Spec)"}\n  ],\n  "answer": "## Scope and Objectives\\nThe **Retirement Planning module** will enable advisors and clients to define retirement goals and formulate a savings and investment plan to achieve them. It covers capturing the client’s financial profile and retirement objectives, computing required contributions, designing an investment strategy, and providing projections up to and through retirement. This module supports multiple goal types (e.g. emergency, education, retirement), with retirement explicitly handled as a distinct goal category ([file-Mnd1bRpJt17LcQfEHEZyXB](file://file-Mnd1bRpJt17LcQfEHEZyXB#:~:text=5%20Goal%20Type%20This%20displays,Wealth)). When a retirement goal is defined, it is linked to the client’s portfolio so the goal’s investments can be tracked and managed in alignment with that purpose ([file-G5PiGEUD6wsJF9vFDtcNFd](file://file-G5PiGEUD6wsJF9vFDtcNFd#:~:text=Basket%20based%20order%20trigger%20%281%29,%E2%97%8F%20Master%20Records)). The solution aims to ensure that the retirement plan is *suitable* for the client’s risk appetite and complies with all regulatory guidelines (e.g. SEBI’s mandates on KYC and investment suitability).\\n\\n## Stakeholders\\n- **Clients (Investors):** End-users whose financial data and retirement objectives are captured. They review the retirement plan and its projections, and benefit from ongoing tracking of goal progress.\\n- **Advisors/Relationship Managers:** Wealth advisors who gather client information, input retirement goals, and use the module to generate and present plans. They initiate any investment orders arising from the plan.\\n- **Supervisors/Compliance Officers:** Oversee and approve proposed plans (maker-checker control) to ensure they meet internal policies and regulatory suitability standards. They have authority to authorize or require changes to the plan before it is finalized  .\\n- **Operations/IT Teams:** Manage data integration (client data, product data) and ensure the module’s outputs (reports, dashboards) are properly generated, stored, and auditable for compliance purposes.\\n\\n## Client Profile & Data Model\\nA comprehensive **client data model** underpins the planning process. The module will utilize existing client profile details including personal demographics (age, current age to infer time to retirement), financial details (income, existing assets, retirement benefits, current investments), liabilities, and family/dependent information. It will also leverage the client’s **KYC status** and **risk profile**. Each client’s risk profile is established via a questionnaire assessing financial situation and risk tolerance ([file-5aRrTupwN6UTT4BNDV7L2r](file://file-5aRrTupwN6UTT4BNDV7L2r#:~:text=navigate%20to%20the%20risk%20profile,Risk%20Profiling)). The risk profile (e.g. Moderate, Aggressive) indicates how much risk the client can take, and is a foundational input to the retirement plan ([file-TbzHuXXUUqd8h6onMDGbjz](file://file-TbzHuXXUUqd8h6onMDGbjz#:~:text=Every%20customer%20will%20have%20a,created%20at%20the%20asset%20level)). If a risk profile is not already on record or is outdated, the advisor must complete the risk profiling process before proceeding ([file-6SMqrxCE3DXF22B5VpMi2J](file://file-6SMqrxCE3DXF22B5VpMi2J#:~:text=12,is%20greater%20than%20customer%20risk)). This ensures alignment with regulatory suitability requirements – for example, the system will not allow proceeding if the client’s risk assessment is missing or expired ([file-6SMqrxCE3DXF22B5VpMi2J](file://file-6SMqrxCE3DXF22B5VpMi2J#:~:text=12,is%20greater%20than%20customer%20risk)). All client data fields needed for the plan (e.g. target retirement age, desired retirement corpus or income, assumed life expectancy, etc.) will have defined validations (e.g. retirement age must be above current age, life expectancy within a reasonable range). Mandatory fields must be filled in, otherwise the system prompts for completion before moving forward ([file-6SMqrxCE3DXF22B5VpMi2J](file://file-6SMqrxCE3DXF22B5VpMi2J#:~:text=12,there%20would%20be%20a%20hard)). \\n\\n## Retirement Goal Definition\\nThe module will provide a dedicated **Goal Definition** interface where the advisor (or client, if using a self-service portal) can set up the retirement goal. Key parameters to capture include:\\n- **Target Retirement Age or Date:** When the client plans to retire.\\n- **Retirement Income/Corpus Goal:** The desired yearly income during retirement, or equivalently the total corpus required by the retirement date. The system may assist in translating an income goal into a corpus based on expected lifespan and withdrawal rate.\\n- **Current Savings for Retirement:** Any assets already earmarked for retirement (e.g. provident fund balances, pension accounts) to factor into the plan.\\n- **Time Horizon:** The number of years until retirement (which is derived from current age and target retirement age) and the duration of the retirement period to plan for (e.g. life expectancy beyond retirement). The time horizon is a critical input that influences asset allocation strategy ([file-TbzHuXXUUqd8h6onMDGbjz](file://file-TbzHuXXUUqd8h6onMDGbjz#:~:text=Figure%203%3A%20Asset%20Allocation%20form,the%20asset%20class%20is%20100)) ([file-TbzHuXXUUqd8h6onMDGbjz](file://file-TbzHuXXUUqd8h6onMDGbjz#:~:text=16,If%20the%20customer)).\\n- **Assumptions:** Planners can input or adjust assumptions like expected inflation rate during accumulation and retirement, and expected rates of return for different asset classes. Default assumption values will be provided (for example, a default investment return rate might be 12% annually, which the user can override based on the client’s expected portfolio mix) ([file-FW8gd42fNtEAxEvSedQDDe](file://file-FW8gd42fNtEAxEvSedQDDe#:~:text=2%20Expected%20Return%20Rate%20%28,4%20Invested%20Amount)) ([file-4cicPP7UemwRK7RbBfT9YF](file://file-4cicPP7UemwRK7RbBfT9YF#:~:text=1%20Monthly%20Investment%20Input%20Numeric,Calculator%20as%20displayed%20in%20the)). These assumptions are documented and can be fine-tuned to create different scenarios (e.g. conservative vs. optimistic growth).\\n- **Contribution Constraints:** Any preferences or constraints on contributions, such as maximum monthly contribution the client can afford, or existing SIP (Systematic Investment Plan) commitments that can be counted toward the goal.\\n\\nThe goal setup screen will allow specifying the goal name (e.g. “Retirement Plan”), and will classify it under the *Retirement* goal type for reporting purposes ([file-Mnd1bRpJt17LcQfEHEZyXB](file://file-Mnd1bRpJt17LcQfEHEZyXB#:~:text=5%20Goal%20Type%20This%20displays,Wealth)). Once the retirement goal details are entered, the system can link this goal to the client’s portfolio structure. In practice, this means any investments made as part of this retirement plan are flagged and grouped under this goal for monitoring. The platform maintains mappings between the customer, their accounts, portfolios and goal identifiers so that goal-linked investments are tracked separately in holdings and reports ([file-G5PiGEUD6wsJF9vFDtcNFd](file://file-G5PiGEUD6wsJF9vFDtcNFd#:~:text=Basket%20based%20order%20trigger%20%281%29,%E2%97%8F%20Master%20Records)) ([file-G5PiGEUD6wsJF9vFDtcNFd](file://file-G5PiGEUD6wsJF9vFDtcNFd#:~:text=The%20mappings%20of%20Customer%2C%20Account%2C,Applicable%20for%20JIO)).\\n\\n## Financial Projections and Calculations\\nWith the goal defined, the module will generate **cash-flow projections** and compute how much the client needs to save and invest to reach the retirement corpus goal. The core calculations and features include:\\n- **Required Contribution Calculation:** Based on the target amount and time available, the system calculates the required monthly or annual contribution. This uses the specified return assumptions to solve for the contribution that, when invested over the accumulation period, will yield the target corpus. For example, a **SIP calculator** can be used: inputting the goal amount, time horizon, 