erage while the original Agent is unavailable or when a short-term workload transfer is needed, with the expectation that ownership remains with the original Agent [2].\n\n- Ownership vs access\n  - Handover transfers ownership and ongoing responsibility for the customer relationship to the receiving Agent; the original owner is no longer the primary owner of those relationships [1].\n  - Delegation grants temporary permission for another Agent to perform actions on behalf of the owner, without changing ultimate ownership or long-term responsibility [2].\n\n- Triggers and authorization/logging\n  - Handover requires explicit authorization and is a formal, typically supervisory-approved change of ownership (e.g., in Maybank’s workflow) [1].\n  - Delegation is designed to be auto-authorized in the system for temporary coverage, enabling quick reallocation of tasks without a formal ownership change [2].\n\n- Data access and scope\n  - Both mechanisms apply to Leads, Prospects, and Clients associated with the Agent hierarchy, but the effect differs: Handover changes who “owns” and manages the relationship; Delegation changes who can perform actions on behalf of the owner while ownership remains with the original Agent [1][2].\n\n- Compliance and continuity\n  - Handover ensures continuity of long-term client management under new ownership when staffing changes occur, with formal tracking of ownership changes for compliance purposes [1].\n  - Delegation ensures continuity of client service during temporary absences, maintaining coverage while preserving the original ownership and accountability structures, with automatic authorization to minimize downtime [2].\n\nSources\n- Maybank_Handover and Delegation_V12_CCV10.pdf\n- HSBC_Handover and Delegation_V10_CCV11.pdf	\N	{"v2_workflow":true,"mode":"concise","model":"gpt-5-nano","seed_node_names":["Supervisor Approval screen","To Approve tab","Wealth Qube","WAT","User Office","Relationship","Folio Master","Portfolio Master","