rarchy List View (often accessed via a left-side icon) to see RMs reporting to you. The system can navigate to a Team Dashboard by default, and you can switch to the Hierarchy List View to drill into a specific RM’s individual dashboard. This establishes the per-RM drill-down path from team-level to individual performance. [2]\n\n3) Open the RM Dashboard for the selected RM\n- In the RM Dashboard (Team Dashboard path), you’ll access the individual RM’s performance metrics and portfolio view. This RM-specific dashboard is the authoritative source for the RM’s performance across leads, conversions, revenue, and activity. [2]\n\n4) Explore performance widgets and apply detailed filters\n- Within the RM dashboard, look for performance widgets such as revenue-range by number of customers and related drill-down capabilities. For example, a RM can view a Revenue Range by Number of Customers widget, with filters including:\n  • No. of Customers – filters all customers mapped to the RM\n  • No. of Customers with Investment Products – filters customers with investments\n  • No. of Customers with Deposit Products – filters deposit customers\n- These widgets typically offer a Three Dots or similar action to drill into Level-3 details for deeper inspection. This enables viewing per-customer or per-segment detail tied to the RM’s performance. [3]\n\n5) Data sources feeding RM performance metrics\n- The RM performance view draws from leads and their statuses (e.g., total leads, client accepted/rejected, in progress, follow-up, new) at the RM level, as seen in Lead/Status figures within the Lead Summary and RM dashboards. In addition, revenue and activity data are surfaced in RM-specific widgets (e.g., revenue-based breakdowns, customer activity) to provide a complete performance picture. [1][3]\n\n6) Security and access considerations for supervisor visibility\n- Access to RM dashboards and supervisor views typically requires a secure login and navigation to an RM Office or supervisor-specific entry point, ensuring that supervisors can view only permitted data (e.g., supervisor dashboards, RM-level dashboards) and that non-wealth or restricted data is excluded as appropriate. This access control is explicitly described in supervisor-dashboard journeys, including login steps and office-based navigation. [4]\n\nPutting it together (typical path): Lead Summary (supervisor view) → Hierarchy List View/Team Dashboard → select RM → RM Dashboard → use RM performance widgets with time/region/RM filters → drill into Level-3 details as needed. [1][2][3][4]\n\nSources\n- JioBlackRock_Journey of Self Assessment and Supervisor Assessment - RM Dashboard_V11_CCV_V10.pdf\n- HSBC_Journey of Self Assessment and Supervisor Assessment - Supervisor Dashboard _V11_CCV_V10.pdf\n- JioBlackRock_Journey of Self Assessment and Supervisor Assessment - RM Dashboard_V10_CCV10.pdf\n- SBI_Journey of Lead to Prospect to Customer_V10_CCV13.pdf	\N	{"v2_workflow":true,"mode":"concise","model":"gpt-5-nano","seed_node_names":["RM","INVESTOR","Order","customer","transaction","Product risk profile","Mutual Funds","Flow Diagram","Minimum Amount/Unit Validation","Systematic Running Status Report"],"seed_node_ids":["system:rmws","dataentity:product_risk_profile","dataentity:mutual_funds","dataentity:investor","report:systematic_running_status_report","dataentity:rm","dataentity:transaction","report:flow_diagram","dataentity:order","dataentity:customer","report:minimum_amount_unit_validation"],"expanded_nodes":60,"expanded_edges":119,"kg_guided_queries":["Previous context ID: 9822b9a5-a913-4ac0-b74b-397d8ecaf176\\n\\nQuestion: [Context-Aware Follow-up Question with Focus Directives]\\n\\nPrevious conversation history is provided for context. Please follow these instructions:\\n\\nSTEP 1 - Context Understanding:\\n• Evaluate if this question contains pronouns or unclear references (e.g., \\"this\\", \\"it\\", \\"that\\", \\"these\\", \\"the above\\")\\n• If such references exist, identi