 = Client Handover** (or similarly named option).  \n   - This upload type is specifically designed to **reassign ownership of multiple client relationships in bulk from one agent to another**.   \n\n3. **Prepare and upload the batch file**  \n   - Prepare a structured file (typically CSV/XLSX) containing, at minimum, identifiers for:  \n     - The clients/relationships to be moved (e.g., client ID / relationship ID), and  \n     - The **new agent/RM** to which they should be reassigned.  \n   - Upload this file under the **Client Handover** upload type.  \n   - On successful upload, the system processes all listed records and applies the ownership change in bulk; **no per‑client manual selection is required in the UI**.  \n\n4. **Review results in the error or upload log**  \n   - After upload, the Operations User can review the **error log/upload log** to confirm which records were successfully handed over and which (if any) failed due to validation issues (e.g., invalid IDs, status constraints).   \n\n5. **Authorization / approval behavior**  \n   - Bulk Client Handover uploads **do not typically require a separate authorization step**; once the file is uploaded successfully, the handover is effected automatically (though this may be configurable per implementation).   \n   - Where an approval workflow is configured for handover actions generally, such items would appear in an authorization or **Pending Approval**–type queue for an Operations checker to review and approve, similar to how other items move from a common **Pending Approval Listing** into a user‑specific approval queue. \n\n### Direct, minimal answer\n\nTo transfer a large number of clients to a new agent without selecting them individually, the Operations User should use the **bulk Client Handover file upload** under the Relationship module, selecting upload type **Client Handover**, uploading a batch file listing all affected clients and the new agent, then verifying the outcome via the error/upload log; this avoids any need for per‑client selection in the UI.   \n\n---\n\n#### Sources\n\n[1] Maybank_Handover and Delegation_V12_CCV10.pdf   \n[2] HSBC_Handover and Delegation_V10_CCV11.pdf   \n[3] JBR_Handover and Delegation_V10_CCV11.pdf   \n[4] SBI_Journey from Order Placement till Settlement_V10_SBI_CCV13.pdf 	\N	{"v2_workflow":true,"mode":"balanced","model":"gpt-5.1","seed_node_names":["User Office","Pending Approval Listing","Supervisor Approval screen","To Approve tab","Batch File","Entitlements","System generated mail","External Systems","Product Cart","Channel Partner"],"seed_node_ids":["datastore:product_cart","system:generated_mail","system:user_office","dataentity:pending_approval_listing","system:external_systems","datastore:batch_file","dataentity:product_cart","dataentity:entitlements","datastore:pending_approval_listing","system:product_cart","system:supervisor_approval_screen","system:pms_app","report:performance_projection","report:product_cart","system:to_approve_tab","dataentity:channel_partner"],"expanded_nodes":95,"expanded_edges":248,"kg_guided_queries":["[Focused Response Directive]\\n\\nPlease follow these instructions when answering:\\n• Answer ONLY the specific question asked - be precise and direct\\n• Include ONLY information that is immediately relevant to this specific question\\n• Exclude tangential details, background context, or loosely related information\\n• Be concise while remaining comprehensive on the core topic\\n• Prioritize clarity and relevance over exhaustive coverage\\n\\nUser's Question: How can an Operations User transfer a large number of clients to a new agent at once without selecting them individually?","What mechanisms exist for bulk reassigning client ownership from one agent to another by an Operations role, without per-client selection?","Describe the platform's supported bulk client transfer workflows for reassigning ownership of multiple client records from an existing agent to a new agent, performed by a