onship Manager.  \n   - For each RM, the supervisor can see:\n     - RM **Name**  \n     - **Total Leads**  \n     - Count of leads by status: **New**, **Ready for Follow-Up**, **In Progress**, **Client Accepted**, **Client Rejected**.\n\n4. **Filter to a Specific RM**  \n   - Use the **search bar** or filter at the top of the table to type an RM’s name.  \n   - The table narrows to that RM, allowing focused review of their lead pipeline and outcomes.\n\nThis drill-down path lets the supervisor move from a consolidated leads snapshot to detailed, RM-by-RM performance metrics with simple dashboard interactions.	{\n  "stepback_intent": "Explain the process for a supervisor to navigate from an overall leads summary dashboard to a detailed view of each Relationship Manager’s performance metrics.",\n  "expanded_question": "What steps and interface actions allow a supervisor to drill down from a high-level leads summary on their dashboard into a detailed performance view for individual Relationship Managers, and what data points and filters are involved in this drill-down?",\n  "business_entities": [\n    "Supervisor Dashboard",\n    "Leads Summary",\n    "Relationship Manager (RM)",\n    "Lead Status by RM view"\n  ],\n  "citations": [\n    {\n      "id": "1",\n      "source": "JioBlackRock_Journey of Self-Assessment and Supervisor Assessment - Supervisor Dashboard"\n    },\n    {\n      "id": "2",\n      "source": "SAAB-Journey of Self_Assessment and Supervisor Assessment_Supervisor Dashboard"\n    }\n  ],\n  "answer": "**Drilling Down from a Lead Summary to Individual RM Performance**\\n\\n1. **High-Level Leads Overview:** On the supervisor’s dashboard, a high-level *Leads* summary widget displays the aggregate leads for all the supervisor’s reportee RMs (e.g. total number of leads and an overview of their statuses) . This gives a consolidated snapshot of team-wide lead activity on the main dashboard.\\n2. **Accessing the Drill-Down Control:** The leads summary widget includes a drill-down option (often a **“More”** icon such as three dots). The supervisor clicks this icon to view more details ([file-8EKNCF34tF4FGXjQfdZc6d](file://file-8EKNCF34tF4FGXjQfdZc6d#:~:text=Internal%20to%20SAB%20Invest%20and,Total%20Leads)). This action indicates the desire to move from the summary view into a more detailed report for leads.\\n3. **Navigating to RM Performance View:** Upon clicking the drill-down, the system opens an intermediate *Lead Status by RM* view (a Level-2 dashboard screen) ([file-8EKNCF34tF4FGXjQfdZc6d](file://file-8EKNCF34tF4FGXjQfdZc6d#:~:text=4,Client%20Rejected)). This view presents a table listing each Relationship Manager under that supervisor, effectively breaking down the high-level lead summary into individual RM performance figures ([file-8EKNCF34tF4FGXjQfdZc6d](file://file-8EKNCF34tF4FGXjQfdZc6d#:~:text=4,Client%20Rejected)).\\n4. **Viewing RM-Level Metrics:** In the *Lead Status by RM* table, each row corresponds to one RM and shows their **Name**, **Total Leads** assigned, and the count of leads in each status category ([file-8EKNCF34tF4FGXjQfdZc6d](file://file-8EKNCF34tF4FGXjQfdZc6d#:~:text=provides%20the%20option%20to%20search,Up)). Key metrics displayed for each RM include the number of **New** leads, **Ready for Follow-Up** leads, **In Progress** leads, **Client Accepted** leads, and **Client Rejected** leads ([file-8EKNCF34tF4FGXjQfdZc6d](file://file-8EKNCF34tF4FGXjQfdZc6d#:~:text=provides%20the%20option%20to%20search,Up)). This breakdown lets the supervisor see how each RM’s leads are progressing through the pipeline.\\n5. **Filtering by RM (Search):** The detailed view also provides a filter to quickly find a specific RM. For instance, a search bar at the top of the table allows the supervisor to type an RM’s name, filtering the list to that individual’s data ([file-8EKNCF34tF4FGXjQfdZc6d](file://file-8EKNCF34tF4FGXjQfdZc6d#:~:text=4,Client%20Rejected)). This makes it easy to focus on one RM’s performance metrics when needed (especially useful if the supervisor oversees many RMs).\\n\\nEach of these steps uses the system’s layered dashboard design to transition from an aggregated leads overview to granular, RM-by-RM performance details. The supervisor starts with a broad leads summary and, via a simple UI interaction, drills down into a dedicated report showing each RM’s lead outcomes and status distribution, with tools like search filters to refine the view ([file-8EKNCF34tF4FGXjQfdZc6d](file://file-8EKNCF34tF4FGXjQfdZc6d#:~:text=Internal%20to%20SAB%20Invest%20and,Total%20Leads)) ([file-8EKNCF34tF4FGXjQfdZc6d](file://file-8EKNCF34tF4FGXjQfdZc6d#:~:text=provides%20the%20option%20to%20search,Up)).\\n\\n**Sources:**\\n1. JioBlackRock Journey of Self-Assessment and Supervisor Assessment – *Supervisor Dashboard* (Lead Summary Drill-Down)\\n2. SAAB Journey of Self-Assessment and Supervisor Assessment – *Supervisor Dashboard* (Lead Status by RM view)"\n}	{"polled":true,"poll_status":"completed","domainResolution":{"domainId":"wealth_management","strategy":"conversation","confidence":1,"matchedKeywords":[]},"jobId":"job_1765952098094_rebazi2et","status":"completed","responseId":"resp_010cd76aeed48c370069424a61499081979c03c6bd65231325","reportFormat":"Custom","mode":"deep","answeredAt":"2025-12-17T06:23:19.953Z"}	resp_010cd76aeed48c370069424a61499081979c03c6bd65231325	t	2025-12-17 06:23:20.847	2025-12-17 06:23:20.847	1	f	\N
