 **each row is an RM**, with columns such as:\n     - RM Name  \n     - Total Leads  \n     - Leads by status: **New**, **Ready for Follow-Up**, **In Progress**, **Client Accepted**, **Client Rejected**\n\n4. **Focus on Specific RMs (Search/Filter)**  \n   - Use the **search bar** or filter at the top of the table to type an RM’s name.  \n   - The list narrows to that RM, allowing the supervisor to review that individual’s lead pipeline and performance.\n\nThis flow lets the supervisor move from a team-wide lead snapshot to a detailed, RM-by-RM performance view using the dashboard’s built-in drill-down and search features.	{\n  "stepback_intent": "Explain the process for a supervisor to navigate from an overall leads summary dashboard to a detailed view of each Relationship Manager’s performance metrics.",\n  "expanded_question": "What steps and interface actions allow a supervisor to drill down from a high-level leads summary on their dashboard into a detailed performance view for individual Relationship Managers, and what data points and filters are involved in this drill-down?",\n  "business_entities": [\n    "Supervisor Dashboard",\n    "Leads Summary",\n    "Relationship Manager (RM)",\n    "Lead Status by RM view"\n  ],\n  "citations": [\n    {\n      "id": "1",\n      "source": "JioBlackRock_Journey of Self-Assessment and Supervisor Assessment - Supervisor Dashboard"\n    },\n    {\n      "id": "2",\n      "source": "SAAB-Journey of Self_Assessment and Supervisor Assessment_Supervisor Dashboard"\n    }\n  ],\n  "answer": "**Drilling Down from a Lead Summary to Individual RM Performance**\\n\\n1. **High-Level Leads Overview:** On the supervisor’s dashboard, a high-level *Leads* summary widget displays the aggregate leads for all the supervisor’s reportee RMs (e.g. total number of leads and an overview of their statuses) . This gives a consolidated snapshot of team-wide lead activity on the main dashboard.\\n2. **Accessing the Drill-Down Control:** The leads summary widget includes a drill-down option (often a **“More”** icon such as three dots). The supervisor clicks this icon to view more details ([file-8EKNCF34tF4FGXjQfdZc6d](file://file-8EKNCF34tF4FGXjQfdZc6d#:~:text=Internal%20to%20SAB%20Invest%20and,Total%20Leads)). This action indicates the desire to move from the summary view into a more detailed report for leads.\\n3. **Navigating to RM Performance View:** Upon clicking the drill-down, the system opens an intermediate *Lead Status by RM* view (a Level-2 dashboard screen) ([file-8EKNCF34tF4FGXjQfdZc6d](file://file-8EKNCF34tF4FGXjQfdZc6d#:~:text=4,Client%20Rejected)). This view presents a table listing each Relationship Manager under that supervisor, effectively breaking down the high-level lead summary into individual RM performance figures ([file-8EKNCF34tF4FGXjQfdZc6d](file://file-8EKNCF34tF4FGXjQfdZc6d#:~:text=4,Client%20Rejected)).\\n4. **Viewing RM-Level Metrics:** In the *Lead Status by RM* table, each row corresponds to one RM and shows their **Name**, **Total Leads** assigned, and the count of leads in each status category ([file-8EKNCF34tF4FGXjQfdZc6d](file://file-8EKNCF34tF4FGXjQfdZc6d#:~:text=provides%20the%20option%20to%20search,Up)). Key metrics displayed for each RM include the number of **New** leads, **Ready for Follow-Up** leads, **In Progress** leads, **Client Accepted** leads, and **Client Rejected** leads ([file-8EKNCF34tF4FGXjQfdZc6d](file://file-8EKNCF34tF4FGXjQfdZc6d#:~:text=provides%20the%20option%20to%20search,Up)). This breakdown lets the supervisor see how each RM’s leads are progressing through the pipeline.\\n5. **Filtering by RM (Search):** The detailed view also provides a filter to quickly find a specific RM. For instance, a search bar at the top of the table allows the supervisor to type an RM’s name, filtering the list to that individual’s data ([file-8EKNCF34tF4FGXjQfdZc6d](file://file-8EKNCF34tF4FGXjQfdZc6d#:~:text=4,Client%20Rejected)). This makes it easy to focus on one RM’s p