he client disagrees, the RM reviews answers or redoes the questionnaire.\n\nAfter confirmation, the system finalizes and saves the risk profile.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Storage, Updates & Linkage to Client Records\n\nOnce determined, the risk profile is stored as part of the client record:\n\n- **Profile record fields**:  \n  - Risk category  \n  - Numeric score (if applicable)  \n  - Assessment date  \n  - Questionnaire version used  \n- **Validity period**:  \n  - Profiles often have an expiry (e.g., 12 months).  \n  - System flags or blocks activity when the profile is expired and prompts re-profiling.  \n- **History**:  \n  - Previous profiles are retained for audit and trend analysis.  \n- **Linkage**:  \n  - The active risk profile is linked to the client and referenced by:  \n    - Portfolio management  \n    - Order placement  \n    - Suitability checks  \n    - Advisory tools\n\nUpdating a profile is done by re-running the questionnaire; old profiles remain in history.\n\n---\n\n## 6. Roles, Permissions & Approvals\n\n- **Who can perform profiling**  \n  - Typically RMs/advisors; sometimes clients via a portal.  \n- **Who can configure questionnaires**  \n  - Restricted to admins/product managers; changes may require supervisory approval.  \n- **Overrides and exceptions**  \n  - If the system allows overriding a computed profile, it must be justified and usually requires manager/compliance approval.  \n- **Access control**  \n  - Only authorized users can view/edit risk profiles.  \n  - Detailed answers may be restricted to compliance/audit roles.\n\n---\n\n## 7. Reporting & Dashboards\n\nThe system uses risk profiles in multiple views and reports:\n\n- **Client-level**  \n  - Risk category shown on client summary and advisory screens.  \n  - Included in proposals and portfolio review reports.\n\n- **Portfolio & suitability reports**  \n  - Show whether asset allocation and product mix align with the client’s risk profile.\n\n- **Management dashboards**  \n  - Distribution of clients by risk category.  \n  - Monitoring of expiring or missing risk profiles.\n\n- **Alerts & notifications**  \n  - Upcoming/expired profiles.  \n  - Portfolios deviating from the client’s risk profile.\n\n- **Documentation**  \n  - Printable/exportable risk profiling report summarizing answers and final category.\n\n---\n\n## 8. Regulatory Compliance & Audit Trail\n\nRisk profiling is central to suitability and KYC requirements:\n\n- **Mandatory step**  \n  - Often required at onboarding and before certain product types or higher-risk investments.\n\n- **Audit trail**  \n  - Logs who performed the assessment, when, which questionnaire version, and the resulting score/category.  \n  - All re-assessments and overrides are timestamped and recorded.\n\n- **Questionnaire records**  \n  - Questions and answers are stored or exportable for internal/external review.\n\n- **Compliance monitoring**  \n  - Reports on profiling coverage, expiries, and investments outside risk tolerance.  \n  - System can enforce periodic re-assessment and track any exceptions or overrides.\n\n---\n\n## 9. Integration with Other Modules\n\nRisk profile data is consumed across the platform:\n\n- **Portfolio management**  \n  - Drives model portfolio selection and target asset allocations per risk category.\n\n- **Product selection & suitability checks**  \n  - Each product has a risk rating.  \n  - System compares product risk vs. client profile:  \n    - May block orders above allowed risk.  \n    - Or show warnings and require explicit confirmation/approval for mild mismatches.\n\n- **Financial planning & advisory tools**  \n  - Use the risk profile to filter and prioritize suitable strategies and products.\n\n- **Order management**  \n  - Before executing new investments, system checks for:  \n    - Existence of a valid risk profile.  \n    - Product–client risk alignment.  \n  - If profile is missing/expired, new purchases are blocked until re-profiling (redemptions may stil