 and the related risk-questionnaire maintenance/context inform how customers can be segmented or prioritized within lead rules [3].\n\n## Defining the criteria (lead rules)\n- Create and configure lead rules that define filter criteria to identify potential targets from the existing customer base. Lead rules can be added, viewed, modified, and used to generate lists (leading to campaign targeting) [2].\n- Rule definitions typically encapsulate the target attributes (e.g., risk tier, asset metrics, location, and other customer attributes) and can be adjusted over time to refine targeting [2].\n\n## Scoring, deduplication, and list management\n- Lead-rule workflows support management actions such as viewing, adding, modifying, and generating lists; advanced workflows may include merging lists to consolidate duplicates or complementary segments (deduplication/merging behavior is indicated by lead-list management capabilities) [2].\n\n## Export and integration with CRM/marketing tools\n- Generated lead lists can be used to drive campaigns and other CRM/marketing activities, enabling export or direct use within campaign workflows and related tools [3].\n\n## Typical workflow (high level)\n1) Define lead criteria as a lead rule (e.g., risk profile band, AUM thresholds, geography, demographics, engagement signals). [2]  \n2) Save and configure the rule, then run Generate List to produce the target-lead set from existing customers. [2]  \n3) Review, adjust, and (if needed) merge/deduplicate multiple lead lists to ensure a clean target set. [2]  \n4) Export the resulting lead list to CRM/marketing tools or use it to drive a campaign in the platform. [3]\n\n## Governance and approvals\n- Changes to lead rules themselves may be governed by standard controls in the platform environment, with downstream approvals managed via the same governance processes that manage risk-profile and questionnaire configurations in related journeys. See risk-profile and lead-management governance patterns in the referenced documents for context. [1][3]\n\n---\nSources: HSBC_Journey of Suspect to Lead_V10_CCV13docx.pdf; JBR_Journey of Suspect to Lead_V10_CCV10docx.pdf; HSBC_Journey of Lead to Prospect to Customer_V11_CCV10.pdf	\N	{"v2_workflow":true,"mode":"concise","model":"gpt-5-nano","seed_node_names":["INVESTOR","RM","customer","risk profiling","Customer Risk profile","Risk Profile Questionnaire","Analytics","Key metrics","Projections","Exposures"],"seed_node_ids":["dataentity:risk_profile_questionnaire","compliance:risk_profiling","system:rmws","dataentity:projections","aum:risk_profiling","dataentity:investor","report:risk_profile_questionnaire","dataentity:risk_profiling","report:exposures","dataentity:analytics","dataentity:rm","system:analytics","dataentity:customer","dataentity:key_metrics","dataentity:exposures","aum:customer_risk_profile"],"expanded_nodes":43,"expanded_edges":57,"kg_guided_queries":["[Focused Response Directive]\\n\\nPlease follow these instructions when answering:\\n• Answer ONLY the specific question asked - be precise and direct\\n• Include ONLY information that is immediately relevant to this specific question\\n• Exclude tangential details, background context, or loosely related information\\n• Be concise while remaining comprehensive on the core topic\\n• Prioritize clarity and relevance over exhaustive coverage\\n\\nUser's Question: How can a user automatically generate a list of target leads based on specific customer criteria?","How can we automatically generate a list of target leads by applying defined customer criteria within the wealth-management platform, including criteria definition, data sources, scoring, and integration options with CRM/marketing tools?","What configuration or workflow enables automatic generation of a target-lead list by applying defined customer criteria (risk profile, AUM, geography, demographics, engagement history), including data sources, rules, scoring, deduplication, and export to CRM/ma